cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR

This paper proposes a new model for convolutional neural networks that is designed for resource-constrained compute platforms such as VR, AR, and wearables. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the benefits of the proposed model for few-shot learning and few-iteration learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper involves training a dictionary and a small set of linear combinations, which may fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, since the paper specifically mentions AR as one of the target platforms, it may also belong to the augmented reality (cs.AR) category.
